ORIGINAL INNOVATIONS

The following design concepts were originated by the author in this project:

1. Forecast-extended price horizon for EV slot scheduling
   Using multi-day ahead hourly price forecasts (e.g. Nordpool Predict FI)
   as a first-class data source, expanded to 15-minute slots and merged with
   confirmed spot prices into a single globally-ranked price series. This
   allows the planner to select slots from a horizon of several days rather
   than being constrained to the ~35-hour confirmed spot window.

2. Dual-deadline EV charging architecture
   Running two independent deadline-bounded optimisations simultaneously:
   - A long-horizon smart deadline (user-set, potentially days ahead) that
     selects the globally cheapest slots across the full available dataset
   - A daily minimum-SOC deadline (configurable hour-of-day) that guarantees
     a minimum state of charge is reached by a fixed time each day as a hard
     safety floor, independently of the long-horizon plan
   This combination enables multi-day cost-optimised charging while
   maintaining a guaranteed daily usability floor — a design not found in
   commercial or open-source EV charging schedulers at the time of writing.

